    <bioghist>The Ann Gridley Chapter of the Daughters of the American Revolution was established in Hillsdale, Michigan in 1911, the thirty-seventh chapter to be organized in the State of Michigan. It was disbanded in 1991.</bioghist>
    <scopecontent>The record group contains the following series: Minutes, 1963-1990, Applications, Administration (by-laws, certificates of membership, disbandment, dues records, and history), Photographs and Scrapbooks. Scrapbook dates include: 1911-1918, 1949, 1940-1959, 1956-1968 (oversized volume) and 1975-1980.</scopecontent>
